New Zealandisation
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the process of phasing out JOINT VENTURES  between New Zealand and foreign fishing companies that followed the declaration of the 200-mile exclusive economic zone, and entailing the acquisition and operation of deep-sea fishing vessels by New Zealand companies.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
