Quote: In 1982 the government took its legislative pen and struck foreign vessels and joint ventures from the tax-credit list ... It was also part of the New Zealandisation process, applying additional pressure on joint ventures to make a commitment to the industry.<i>Ibid.</i> 351 By 1981 the major fishing companies ... were building up substantial fleets. Initially, much of their catching capacity had been through joint ventures, but increasingly they used their own vessels ... While this investment set the foundation for the New Zealandisation of the deepwater fishery, it increased pressure on the inshore fishery.
